properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued January 8 at 2:41AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
STRONG AND GUSTY WINDS TO 55 MPH POSSIBLE THIS AFTERNOON AND
EVENING...

The high Wind Watch that was in effect for portions of eastern
Wyoming has been cancelled. Strong wind gusts will still be
possible this afternoon and evening ahead of a strong cold front
and Pacific storm system. West winds of 25 to 35 mph with gusts
to 55 mph will be possible across portions of eastern Wyoming and
western Nebraska. Winds will increase late this morning, peak
this afternoon and evening, before relaxing late this evening and
early Thursday morning. Use caution if you are driving as strong
crosswinds may develop on north south routes. Secure loose outdoor
items as they may be blown about. For additional info please see
the latest High Wind Warning.
